The trick in this problem is realizing that the operations are a distraction.

Key Insight
Consider one character:
aaaaa
Using the allowed operations, you can keep deleting neighboring occurrences until only:
a
remains.
You can never remove the last 'a', because every operation requires another 'a' to exist as the reference character.

Therefore:

Every distinct character can be reduced to exactly one occurrence.
Example:
baadccab
Distinct characters:
b
a
d
c
Count:
4
So answer:
4
No simulation needed.
