Interview Discussion
A lot of candidates get trapped into trying to simulate deletions:
find closest left
find closest right
delete
repeat
which becomes complicated.
The interviewer is testing whether you can spot the invariant:

Only the number of distinct characters matters.
Alternative Solution (Frequency Array)
Since there are only lowercase letters:
class Solution {
    public int minimizedStringLength(String s) {
        boolean[] seen = new boolean[26];
        int count = 0;

        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (!seen[c - 'a']) {
                seen[c - 'a'] = true;
                count++;
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
}
